    "wikipediaUrl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buffalo_Lithia_Water",
    "extract": "Buffalo Lithia Water was a brand of lithia water bottled in Buffalo Lithia Springs, Virginia. It was advertised with outsize medical claims, including the ability to treat fevers and nervous disorders. One ad promised a \"Marvelous Efficiency in Gout, Rheumatism, [and] Gastrointestinal Dyspepsia.\" It was sold from the late 19th century to the 1950s. At the height of its popularity, it was available in approximately 20,000 groceries and pharmacies in Europe, Canada, and the United States."
